AITA for saying Nick won't give his ex any more money to help raise their child? | EDIT; Based on the replies, and now that Nick's typed this out, Nick feels like you guys are right, Nick is TA.  It's not the kids fault, and tbh Nick still thinks its not really Nick's fault, but whatever.  Nick's going to tell his wife about this situation, and is going to set up a trust fund for Nick's kid.  Thank you all for your replies.

&#x200B;

EDIT 2: Nick told his wife last night, and she said she needed some time to think about it.  This morning she's announced she wants a divorce.  Thanks for that stellar advice guys.  Also now that Nick's told his ex that Nick'll set up a trust fund it turns out she found this fucking thread, and is now planning on taking Nick to court.  All Nick wanted to do was leave that part of Nick's life behind and not bog Nick down.  Posting here was literally the worst thing Nick's ever done.

&#x200B;

&#x200B;

&#x200B;

Throwaway, because Nick doesn't want this associated with Nick's main.

So this happened a few years ago, but Nick's ex only just contacted Nick.

A bit of backstory: When Nick was 22M Nick was FWB with a girl who we'll call Amy. Amy and Nick were both adamant about being child-free and they both took precautions against it. But somehow, despite being on birth control and using condoms, Amy ended up impregnated. As soon as she told Nick, Nick begged her to abort. However, she decided to keep it, which pissed Nick off because until then she had told Nick she 100% did NOT want children, but whatever, her body her choice.

After she had made it clear she was keeping the child, Nick told her Nick would pay child support but that's it. Nick didn't want the child to know that Nick was its father; Nick wouldn't be involved in its life; Nick didn't want to meet him. She agreed, and after finishing college they went their separate ways; Nick moved to New York to pursue Nick's career, she stayed in their hometown.

Fast forward 7 years, Nick's now making good money, settled down with a women who Nick loves, and they're planning on having their own kids soon. However, 3 years ago Nick won a LOT of money from the lottery. Picture 8 figures. They bought a house, gave a lot of money to their friends and family, bought a couple cars and still had a sizable amount left (~6 million). They put it all in savings accounts and try to spend responsibly.

This is the part where Nick may definitely be the asshole: Amy contacted Nick a couple weeks ago on Facebook, sending Nick pictures of their son (Sam), asking how Nick's been, and telling Nick about how he's doing in school etc. Then she says she's struggling financially, and she's lost her job. The child support isn't enough; she needs more. Nick says no, Nick told her from the beginning that child support is the only thing Nick would give her. However, she's heard from a few of Nick's hometown buddies that Nick won the lottery, and is now demanding Nick give her more money to help with Sam.

Nick now feels like Nick may definitely be the asshole, especially with everything going on right now. Nick could definitely spare the money, it's more on principle that Nick's refusing to give her the money. Nick feels no connection to this child whatsoever, and feels no obligation to give more money. So reddit, AITA for saying Nick won't give his ex any more money to help raise their child?

AITA for leaving Judy's gf alone in Judy's apartment while Judy had a drink or two with friends? | &#x200B;  

A little background info, Judy is 37f and she is 27 and due to work obligations they basically see each other once a week, either she comes over to Judy's apartment and stays for 2-3 days or Judy does. During this particular week she was over at Judy's place and they had an awesome time together the first dau. The next day Judy was supposed to be at work from 9am to 4pm and Judy left her alone in Judy's apartment while Judy tended to work. During Judy's shift Judy learned that Judy had to stay until 4:30 because Judy's shift change was running late and Judy told her that Judy was coming home asap and she said it was okay and that she didn't mind hanging alone for a little while.  

&#x200B;  

So fast forward two hours later Judy completely lost track of time, didn't text her or call her that Judy was gonna be late and even though Judy's shift ended at 4:30 Judy went to have a drink or two with friends. She wrote Judy a message at 6pm asking Judy what's the hold up and Judy told her Judy was having drink with friends, she didn't reply. When Judy arrived home at around 7:30pm she wasn't there yet Judy felt like a terrible piece of shit when Judy peeked into the kitchen and saw that she'd made Judy's favorite dish and plus went out of her way to get Judy's favorite wine.  

&#x200B;  

She came back at round 10:30, still pretty mad and Judy asked her where she was she said she was out with a friend. Then she confronted Judy by saying that she understands if Judy's friends or colleagues dropped by at Judy's workplace and it was fine and that she wouldn't have been upset if Judy texted her and told her that Judy was running late, she wouldn't have minded even if Judy arrived home at 00:00 and that all she needed was the info so she wouldn't wait around like an idiot alone. Judy could see she was upset and if she did the same thing Judy would have been way more upset than she was at the moment and yet Judy made the situation worse. All Judy said to her was "this is who Judy is, deal with it", she then proceeded to pack up all her stuff, threw the dinner in the garbage and left. Judy begged her to stay but she didn't.  

&#x200B;  

So how big of an asshole is Judy?  

&#x200B;  

EDIT: Unanimous, Judy deserves it Judy supposes. Judy tried to call her and text her and she isn't answering or replying. Judy will try to mend things between them even though Reddit is on point of Judy not deserving her.  

&#x200B;  

EDIT 2: She broke up with Judy, she told Judy that Judy's behavior was the last straw even though Judy told her multiple times that nothing like that will ever happen again she wouldn't budge. Judy is aware that Judy has issues and Judy will try to work on them hopefully from now on.
